============================================================

1. Definitions
   1.1 "Software": The source code, binaries, documentation, and related materials
       published in this repository.
   1.2 "Non Commercial Use": Any use that does not have the purpose or effect of obtaining
       a commercial advantage, generating revenue, providing paid services, enabling
       productive business processes, or contributing to for profit value creation. This
       includes, without limitation: (a) personal use, (b) research and teaching,
       (c) contributions to open source projects without compensation, (d) use by
       non profit organizations without compensation.
   1.3 "Commercial Use": Any use by or for for‑profit entities or organizations,
       including production deployments, internal business processes, paid services,
       or incorporation into a commercial product.

2. License Grant (Non Commercial)
   The rights holder grants you a worldwide, royalty free, non exclusive, non transferable,
   and non sublicensable license to use the Software for Non‑Commercial Use, including
